                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d793">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Braden</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-09T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 9, 1945—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>86. For Davis from Gardiner and Fraser FEA. Your 71, February 3. We wish you to
                    maintain position that USCCA is immune from suit and therefore not liable for
                    claims outlined in your cable, unless Embassy has strong objections.</p>
                <p>Following your full report, we will give consideration to union’s demand for
                    contract in accordance with your wishes. [Gardiner and Fraser.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
